## What this is

{{intent_long_description}}

This project is scaffolded with the **system-designer SDD methodology**: every artifact is a living document, every session ends in a HITL checkpoint, every prompt is audited via prompt-architect, and every decision carries calibrated probabilities. See `CLAUDE.md` for the orchestrator contract and `SPEC.md` for the spec.

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Read the orchestrator contract
cat CLAUDE.md

# 2. Read the spec
cat SPEC.md

# 3. Inspect current state
cat tracking/project.json | jq

# 4. List sessions
ls tracking/sessions/

# 5. Resume the orchestrator (in any LLM with file-system access)
#    Drop this folder into the LLM and prompt:
#    "Continue {{system_name}} from current state."
```

## Project structure

```
{{system_name}}/
├── CLAUDE.md                 # orchestrator contract
├── README.md                 # you are here
├── SPEC.md + SPEC.json       # what we build
├── ARCHITECTURE.md           # how we build
├── HANDOFF.md                # generator handoff (read once)
├── tracking/                 # living: project state, sessions, KPIs, errors, decisions
├── memory/                   # living: user prefs, project context, feedback, refs
├── audit/                    # living: EU AI Act audit sheet (incremental), self-audits, reflections
├── docs/                     # decisions (ADRs), architecture, reports (IMRaD/TRIPOD-AI)
├── library_docs/             # fresh docs of every pinned library
├── src/                      # the system
├── tests/                    # tests + golden + adversarial
├── tools/                    # custom scripts and prompts
└── .claude/                  # optional convenience layer (skills, agents, settings)
```

